channel.title: I think I am going to lose my mind
channel.description:
Alright. So I've been coding lots since yesterday. Everything was great and I was even considering opening up my new server earlier than expected. I was very pleased to see my progress since a couple weeks ago and I wanted to test out one of the new updates that I made, which was a custom made farming. So I clicked on run&compile, pressed C, hit enter, AND THEN!:
[code] client.java:19917: illegal start of expression } ^ 1 error Files Compiled Successfully! Press any key to continue . . . [/code]
This has been driving me to the brink of insanity since yesterday. I will calmly tell you now that I am about to lose it. I even ended up deleting everything that I added JUST so that I didn't have to look at this error anymore.. But it still shows up..EVERY TIME I compile my server. I haven't the slightest clue what happened and I bet it's probably something extremely simple to fix.. But I can't. Can you help me achieve my goal and stop this madness?
